<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-12-12T13:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-12-12T13:41:00-05:00" n="405" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d405">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.56273: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tobin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">The
                                        Hague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-12-12T19:00:00+00:19"><hi rend="italic">December 12,
                                        1923—7 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received December
                                13.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>68. Department’s telegram 60, December 7, 10 a.m. Have just received the
                            note from the Netherlands Minister for Foreign Affairs: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“I have great pleasure in informing you that on our side there is
                                    no objection to the new treaty of commerce being negotiated at
                                    Washington. We are informing Monsieur de Graeff. Signed Van
                                    Karnebeek.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Tobin</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>